message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The presentation of the rash is consistent with impetigo, a bacterial skin infection. The most common complication of impetigo is bacterial superinfection of skin lesions, which can lead to cellulitis, sepsis or even necrotizing fasciitis. Pneumonia, encephalitis, and cerebellar ataxia are not commonly associated with impetigo.

The most common complication of scabies is bacterial superinfection of skin lesions, as the skin is already compromised by the mite infestation. While rare, scabies can also lead to encephalitis or cerebellar ataxia, but these are more severe complications and not as common as bacterial superinfection. Pneumonia is not a complication of scabies.
